<br>
<br>
-You start fully rested.  In this state, you gain a bonus on all xp gained from killing mobs.  <br>
<br>
-As you fight, your rest level decreases, and your experience bonus decreases.  <br>
<br>
-Eventually, you become fatigued, and actually start receiving an xp penalty.<br>
<br>
-Energy is recovered by logging out or resting in inns placed in various cities and outposts.  I believe it's something like 8 hours (atm) to return to fully rested from completely fatigued.  I foresee these inns as good spots to form pickup groups, hock wares, and trade quest items, just like the good old days of the EC tunnel.  I used to log out every night in that tunnel, anyway.<br>
