<br>
1. Increase the time it takes to reach max level: Blizzard is not going to be pushing out expansion packs as fast as SOE. Would you not be disappointed if you reached 60 and great gear in less than 6 weeks? Game longevity suffers as a result.<br>
<br>
2. Remove excess money from the economy: Because the rest system has Inns located at major and minor cities, players will pay for transportation to these locations, taking excess gold out of the economy.<br>
<br>
Con's of the Rest System:<br>
<br>
1. Makes Blizzard look like Big Brother: People are enraged that this system is akin to Blizzard telling you when to play, and how to play. That's fairly accurate, except that you can continue to gain exp when not full rested (see next point).<br>
<br>
